snippet.textDisplay: I had to have my 1st daughter via c section due to her being breached as well, come to find out i have a rare shaped bicornuate uterus so my daughter basically had very little room to turn. My 2nd ended up turning head down but there were so many risks having a VBAC so i decided a c section was best. & honestly my 2nd csection was 1000x worse than my 1st. Sometimes you cant plan what you want cause then you get your hopes up when things cant go that way. You just have to do whats brings baby girl out healthy & be strong! Some babies also stay breached up until they're READY to turn TO BE BORN! 😊 my niece stood breached until 38 weeks & then my sisters water broke few days later. 🤷🏻‍♀️🙌🏻 prayers! Dont think too much of it just let things happen as they're meant to!
